The paper discusses the complexity analysis of optimizing balloon drawings of rooted trees, which involves various aspects of computational geometry such as angular resolution, aspect ratio, and standard deviation of angles. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with the optimization of tree structures, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The analysis of the different types of balloon drawings and their complexity can be considered as a graph theory problem, which is covered in cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the paper discusses approximation algorithms, which can be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
